{
  "texts": [
    "In Fig. 4(c), we present the histogram of effective clock angles, i.e., the phases of m, obtained from multiple CMC snapshots.",
    "As before, in the Z + 8 AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM phase (T = 0.08), these angles take values corresponding to even multiples of π/8.",
    "In contrast, within the emerging Z - 8 AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM phase (T = 0.11), the angles are centered around odd multiples of π/8 -values that are forbidden by the microscopic Hamiltonian (1).Similar to the q = 6 case, this emergence can be understood by examining the distribution of local clock angles on a √ 2 × √ 2 sublattice from a single CMC snapshot, as shown in Fig. 4(d).",
    "In the Z + 8 AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM phase, the (e) Real-space snapshots of clock states k ∈ {0,1,...,q -1} for q = 8 obtained from CMC for a system of linear size L = 64.",
    "Snapshots are shown for the phases: Z + q AFM ⊕ Z2 NM (T /J1 = 0.08), Z - q AFM ⊕ Z2 NM (T /J1 = 0.11), QLRO ⊕ Z2 NM (T /J1 = 0.20), and PM (T /J1 = 0.39)."
  ]
}